<br>
If ya need to spread over 6 different ones, I'd put:<br>
RM - more innate RM does not hurt.<br>
WIS - if only there's spare gear to switch around.<br>
STR/AGI/STA - depending on what's needed.<br>
<br>
AGI - Dorfs have lower base AGI but the target of 80 AGI is easy to obtain.<br>
STR - for clerics who dont have weight reducing bags at 60.<br>
STA - more hp never hurts. <br>
<br>
RM/RC/RD/RP/INT/CHA = low priority. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7A3412><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uadonborealis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adon Borealis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tunare's n00b</span><br>  Posts: 462<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(12/19/01 4:15:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=72.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://faceweb-004.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/10/2273510.jpg Height=160 Width=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So, with new cleric skills</span><hr size=1> I don't think having &quot;critical heals&quot; really means dick all personally. Faster casting times would rock, but more healing on a divine light or a remedy once in a blue moon is not necessary!<br>
